<dl id="n36204h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36204h">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36204h"> 204(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Bible Belt</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Spiritualism]</font> Throughout what is now widely called <mark>the Bible belt</mark> men, women, and children mounted on benches and began to shout in strange tongues. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 32</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
